                   analysis confirms that these data can be used to
                   study common and idiosyncratic brain response
                   patterns to complex auditory stimulation. Among the
                   potential uses of this dataset are the study of
                   auditory attention and cognition, language and music
                   perception, and social perception. The auxiliary
                   measurements enable a large variety of additional
                   analysis strategies that relate functional response
                   patterns to structural properties of the brain.
